.TH il-verify 1 "Viper" "Viper il-verify" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
il\-verify \- verify a Viper IL module
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B il\-verify
 [\-\-version] <file.il>
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B il\-verify
parses and verifies a Viper IL module from disk. It reports structural and
semantic issues per the IL specification (types, control flow, memory, EH).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and build information (tool and IL spec versions).
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success (verification passed); non-zero on any error, including
I/O failures and verification diagnostics.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Verify a module:
.RS
.nf
il-verify examples/hello.il
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ilc (1),
.BR il\-dis (1)
